results.title: Now! The most deadly mystic combat of all!  Doctor Strange versus Doctor Strange?!
Doctor Stranger Yet! (title on page 26)
results.description: Strange pulls demon from his chest which caused his erratic behavior.  The world, remade by The Creators, has gone mad.  Strange battles his bizarre wild-boar counterpart Dr. Stranger Yet.

results.title: A Gathering of Fear!
results.description: vs the Dweller in Darkness, an other-dimensional demon.

results.title: A Death  for Immortality
results.description: vs Alaric who wields the Atlantean Sword of Kamuu.  with the Sub-Mariner.

results.title: All My Dreams Against Me
results.description: vs the Dweller and Dream Weaver from last issue.

results.title: A Midsummer's Nightmare!
results.description: vs Cyrus Black, a magician from Defenders #6, and Nightmare

results.title: Of Knights--and Pawns
results.description: with the Avengers, as DS attempts to revive the Black Knight whose statue form  was shattered in Avengers 157.  vs the Dweller, who again works through agents.  This time he uses Ludi, a demon to do his bidding.

results.title: The Man Who Knew Stephen Sanders!
results.description: vs Ningal, brother demon to last issue's Ludi.  The threads of this character come from Chamber of Chills 4.  This continues  the story of the Dweller.

results.title: Weep for the Soul of Man...
The Power of Dr. Strange!
results.description: with Brother Voodoo, featuring an origin re-cap.  vs Damballah.  Intro Morganna Blessing, a passer-by with a slight ability in the occult who becomes a supporting character.

results.title: A Time For Love, A Time For  Hate!
Land of the Pharaohs
results.description: with the Fantastic Four, vs Rama- Tut.  The cover reprises the original cover of FF which first features Rama-Tut.  vs Nightmare.  The action takes   place during the FF's first meeting  with Rama-Tut.  Clea leaves Dr Strange.

results.title: A Mystic  Reborn!
results.description: origin recap.  vs Demonicus (from Strange Tales 128), Adria, and Kaecilius (minions of Mordo.)  All three last defeated in ST 143.
